If I hadrt already packed my letter opener,
I'd give you such a stabbing.

14:48.487 --> 14:50.751
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Whoa, Ray.

14:50.856 --> 14:53.620
Are we gonna let politics get
in the way of our friendship?

14:53.726 --> 14:58.823
Friendship? You told people
I lured children into my gingerbread house.

14:58.931 --> 15:01.229
[Chuckles]
Yeah. That was just a lie.

15:01.333 --> 15:03.824
Simpson, the American people...

15:03.936 --> 15:06.962
have never tolerated incompetence
in their public officials.

15:07.072 --> 15:11.532
You are going
to crash and burn...

15:11.644 --> 15:13.703
my fatheaded friend.

15:13.812 --> 15:16.940
See? We're still friends.
Come on. Give us a cuddle.

15:19.084 --> 15:20.984
<i>Jean-Raul, how are</i>
<i>the new uniforms?</i>

15:21.086 --> 15:23.554
Do they match the suede boots?
Beautiful.

15:23.656 --> 15:26.716
Did you get the new trucks?
Are they amphibious?

15:26.825 --> 15:29.020
Well, there's only
one way to find out.

15:29.128 --> 15:31.460
We can always buy more.

15:31.563 --> 15:33.554
Wow, Dad.
You're really working hard.

15:33.666 --> 15:37.659
Yes, I gotta work hard, honey.
Daddy made a lot of"crazy promises."

15:37.770 --> 15:39.738
I'm really proud of you, Homie...

15:39.838 --> 15:43.069
but can the garbageman
really do all the things you said?

15:43.175 --> 15:46.770
Oh, the garbageman can,
Marge.

15:46.879 --> 15:49.404
The garbageman can.

15:56.388 --> 15:59.653
## [Singing]

16:03.996 --> 16:07.397
## [Singing Continues]

16:15.240 --> 16:18.107
<i>##[Singing Continues]</i>

16:20.179 --> 16:21.578
[Chuckles]

16:21.680 --> 16:24.911
## [Singing Continues]

16:28.520 --> 16:33.014
## [Singing Continues]

16:40.466 --> 16:42.366
## [Singing Continues]

16:57.850 --> 16:59.875
## [Singing Continues]

17:01.887 --> 17:04.856
## [Singing Continues]

17:12.897 --> 17:15.731
## [Singing Ends]

17:15.834 --> 17:16.335
[Cheering]

17:16.335 --> 17:16.960
[Cheering]

17:23.108 --> 17:24.973
- [Humming]
- Simpson, you idiot!

17:25.077 --> 17:27.068
You spent your entire year's budget
in a month! Your department's broke!

17:27.179 --> 17:29.204
[Gasps]
Oh, no!

17:29.314 --> 17:32.215
Wait! I think I've got
the perfect solution.

17:32.317 --> 17:34.717
You better, because
those garbagemen...

17:34.820 --> 17:36.720
- won't work for free.
- D'oh!

17:36.822 --> 17:39.256
<i>Oh, Ratterson was right.</i>

17:39.358 --> 17:42.486
I'm crashing and burning!
Crashing and burning!

17:42.594 --> 17:45.529
How could you spend
$4.6 million in a month?

17:45.631 --> 17:49.795
They let me sign checks with a stamp,
Marge. A stamp!

17:49.902 --> 17:52.427
You know, Dad,
there's a lesson in all this.

17:52.538 --> 17:56.770
Many cities have problems with garbage
disposal, and it's time you realize you can't-

17:56.875 --> 18:00.038
Wait! Shut up!
I just thought of something.

18:02.281 --> 18:05.182
- <i>[Vehicle Engine Starts]</i>
- <i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

18:06.785 --> 18:08.514
[Whistling]

18:09.621 --> 18:11.521
Morning, boys.

18:11.623 --> 18:13.818
- Where's our paychecks, you bum?
- [Men Grumbling]

18:13.926 --> 18:16.451
My men ain't workir
another minute till we get paid.

18:16.562 --> 18:20.020
- Will cash be okay?
- Will it?

18:20.132 --> 18:22.225
Did I hear a, uh,
briefcase opening?

18:23.936 --> 18:25.836
Okay, before I show you...

18:25.938 --> 18:29.101
- who wants to guess how I got the money?
- Dealing drugs?

18:29.208 --> 18:31.005
- Drugs?
- I'll have to say drugs too.

18:31.110 --> 18:33.010
Close, but you're way off.

18:44.490 --> 18:46.390
Look at that beautiful garbage.

18:46.492 --> 18:48.892
Other cities don't want it,
so they pay me to dump it...

18:48.994 --> 18:50.894
in this old abandoned mine.

18:50.996 --> 18:55.126
- That's awful! I almost wish it were drugs.
- Some of it is.

18:58.003 --> 19:01.063
Good God, Homer.
You're turning our wonderful little town...

19:01.173 --> 19:03.073
into America's trash hole.

19:03.175 --> 19:07.009
Marge!
lxnay on the ash holetray.

19:07.112 --> 19:10.013
But, Dad, you can't cram garbage
under Springfield forever.

19:10.115 --> 19:12.015
Sure, I can, honey kitten.

19:16.488 --> 19:18.513
<i>[Birds Chirping]</i>

19:18.624 --> 19:20.592
I don't know
how you did it, Homer...

19:20.692 --> 19:23.183
but you certainly solved
that budget crisis.

19:23.295 --> 19:25.286
[Liquid Gurgles]

19:25.397 --> 19:27.763
What the hell is that?

19:27.866 --> 19:30.198
Uh, nothing.

19:30.302 --> 19:32.600
Now, uh, you were saying
how great I was.

19:32.704 --> 19:34.934
[Liquid Gurgles]

19:35.040 --> 19:37.235
[Grunts]

19:37.342 --> 19:39.776
What's this?
Melon rinds, panty hose...

19:39.878 --> 19:42.176
a term paper from Texas Tech?

19:42.281 --> 19:44.943
Simpson, do you know
anything about-

19:47.486 --> 19:51.354
Dear Lord, please take
Mr. Bunny up to heaven.

19:51.456 --> 19:54.016
- [Ground Rumbling]
- <i>[All Scream]</i>

19:54.126 --> 19:56.026
[Rumbling Continues]

19:56.128 --> 20:01.065
Hey, Brandine, I think
I done busted my stink bone.

20:01.166 --> 20:03.760
- [Rumbling Continues]
- [Gasping]

20:03.869 --> 20:06.565
[Tires Screeching]

20:09.975 --> 20:12.739
- [Crowd] Aye.
- And all those opposed...

20:12.844 --> 20:14.903
to horsewhipping
Homer Simpson?

20:16.248 --> 20:18.739
- Nay.
- And now, all in favor...

20:18.850 --> 20:20.909
of reinstating Ray Patterson?

20:21.019 --> 20:23.920
Yea!

20:24.022 --> 20:27.890
## [Jazz]

20:27.993 --> 20:31.258
[Panting] Oh.
[Chuckles]

20:31.363 --> 20:33.331
Oh, gosh. You know...

20:33.432 --> 20:36.424
I'm not much on speeches,
but it's so gratifying...

20:36.535 --> 20:38.935
to leave you wallowing
in the mess you've made.

20:39.037 --> 20:41.437
You're screwed.
Thank you. Bye.

20:41.540 --> 20:44.873
## [Jazz]

20:44.977 --> 20:47.445
He's right.
He ain't much on speeches.

20:47.546 --> 20:50.606
Now, people,
we are far from screwed.

20:50.716 --> 20:53.116
- <i>[Ground Rumbling]</i>
- Aaah!

20:53.218 --> 20:55.652
- [Sputtering]
- [Crowd Gasps]

20:55.754 --> 20:58.086
Time for panic has come.

20:58.190 --> 21:01.626
We must move forward and turn to
the towrs all-purpose contingency plan.

21:01.727 --> 21:05.458
- You mean Plan "B"?
- Yes. "B."

21:08.567 --> 21:12.094
- [Crunching]
- I can't believe it's come to this.

21:12.204 --> 21:14.104
Come to what?

21:14.206 --> 21:17.266
Moving the whole town
five miles down the road.

21:17.376 --> 21:19.867
<i>It's crazy!</i>

21:19.978 --> 21:23.243
- Yeah, it's something, all right.
- So we transplant the town.

21:23.348 --> 21:25.578
We're just gonna trash
the new Springfield too.

21:25.684 --> 21:29.120
Yeah, but what are you gonna do?
If you need me, I'll be at Moe's.

21:29.221 --> 21:31.815
- [Grunts] Hi, Moe.
- <i>[Moe] Hey, Homer.</i>

21:39.765 --> 21:43.098
Do yourself a favor.
Don't turn around.

21:43.201 --> 21:45.761
- [Flies Buzzing]
- [Squeaking]

21:45.871 --> 21:50.774
<i>[Man Screaming]</i>

21:50.876 --> 21:53.037
<i>[Man #2]</i>
<i>I told you not to turn around.</i>

22:15.734 --> 22:18.294
## [Strumming]

22:18.403 --> 22:22.305
Look, guys. I got a Springfield spoon
for my spoon collection.

22:22.407 --> 22:24.898
Oh, here we go.

22:25.010 --> 22:27.478
How many spoons have you
got now, Adam?

22:27.579 --> 22:30.878
Nine. If I didn't have my spoons,
I'd go insane.

22:30.982 --> 22:33.007
Can I see it?

22:33.118 --> 22:34.585
- [Gasps]
- My spoon!

22:34.686 --> 22:36.153
- Ow!
- <i>[Spoon Clatters]</i>

22:36.254 --> 22:38.449
Wankers.

22:38.557 --> 22:40.525
- [Murmuring]
- Shh!

